title: Global youth unemployment rate until 2019
summary: In general Youth unemployment rate has stayed the same over the Year.
Youth unemployment rate is slightly increasing from 2014 to 2016, and finally roughly constant from 2016 to 2017.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2014 and 2015.
Maximum Youth unemployment rate, about 13.2 was reported at Year 2016, and 2017
The lowest Youth unemployment rate, of value 13.0 was reported at Year 2014
